      "markdown": "# TechQA: A Practical Beginner's Course\n\n**Purpose:** Ensure software quality through testing and validation.\n\n## Course Overview\n\n**Who this is for:** Beginners stepping into software quality assurance who need to understand how testing fits into the way software actually gets built, when to plan tests, what \"quality\" even means in a testable sense, before touching any specific tool or automation framework.\n\n**How the course works:** This module covers QA Fundamentals in three topics. Every topic follows the same pattern:\n- **Concept** - what it is, in plain language\n- **Structure at a Glance** - the core building blocks you'll actually work with\n- **Where you'd actually use this** - a real business scenario\n- **Lab** - hands-on, buildable exercises\n- **Checkpoint**\n- **Quiz** - five questions with answers\n\n**Tools needed:** None yet. This module is about the concepts and life cycles that every later, tool-specific module (test management tools, bug trackers, automation frameworks) will assume you already know.\n\n---\n\n"
